snippet.textDisplay:
CHROMATICA/STUPID LOVE THEORY
"The world rots in conflict. Many tribes battle for dominance. While the Spiritual ones pray and sleep for peace, the Kindness punks fight for Chromatica..."


I. Chromatica
So we now know that Chromatica is not just the name of the planet and its world depicted in the video, but its also the name of the album.


II. Tribes
Several tribes are depicted in the video and each is understood by the color they wear and embody. Each time a tribe is introduced a small coin/seal appears on screen which is engraved with the symbol of the tribe it heralds. As of now we have (in order of appearance) Pink, Black, Yellow, Green, Blue, Red. Each is also differentiated by the materials they wear which are specific to them: The Blue tribe is in denim every which way, the Green tribe is covered in wildlife foliage, the Yellow tribe is wearing something like tracksuits, The Black tribe is wearing leather, fishnets, hardware, The Red tribe is wearing these sort of smock capes without much underneath.


III. Kindness Punks
This, the Pink tribe, is Gaga's tribe and I think it's safe to assume she is their leader. Their goal is to foster peace between the tribes.


IV. Stupid Love
This song is centered on the Kindness Punks and their beliefs. It begs the question as to whether or not the concept behind the album "Chromatica", which is this world she has built, will not be told through each song representing and embodying on of the tribes/colors. The symbol for the Kindness Punks is the first we see, the only on which is full screen and it is on the underside of the logo for Stupid Love.


Of course this begs the question: Is Chromatica a visual album!?


V. Social Commentary
Interesting to note is that the only actual conflict shown in the video are between the Blue and the Red tribes, who are also the last introduced. If you're American you know what that means, if you're not it's simple: Blue is the color of the Democratic party and Red is the color of the Republican party. And Gaga steps in to break up their fight by neutralizing them both and then bringing everyone together in joyful dancing. Maybe this music is the medicine she believe can be a remedy to our hearts after almost 5 years of bitter divide and hostility in the sociopolitical fabric of this country.


VI. Chromatica Logo
The logo for Chromatica appears three times in the video and the last one is at the very end. However, the first two times it shows up in the video the choreography has drastically changed and the frenetic pace is gone. The first time it appears, the choreography has totally shifted to slow, harmonious movements as she leads the Yellow tribe back to the Black tribe in order to "find that peace". The second time all the tribes are together and everyone is stock still.


Okay, that's what I've got for now. What do y'all think?
